The '''1990 [[Tel Aviv Open|Riklis Classic]]''' was a [[tennis]] tournament played on [[hard court]]s that was part of the [[ATP World Series|World Series]] of the [[1990 ATP Tour]]. It was played at the [[Israel Tennis Centers]] at [[Ramat HaSharon]] near [[Tel Aviv]] in [[Israel]] from October 8 through October 15, 1990.

==Champions==
===Men's Singles===
{{main|1990 Riklis Classic – Singles}}
{{flagicon|URS}} '''[[Andrei Chesnokov]]''' defeated {{flagicon|ISR}} [[Amos Mansdorf]] 6&ndash;4, 6&ndash;3
* It was Chesnokov's 2nd title of the year and the 6th of his career.

===Men's Doubles===
{{main|1990 Riklis Classic – Doubles}}
{{flagicon|NGR}} '''[[Nduka Odizor]]''' / {{flagicon|RSA|1928}} '''[[Christo van Rensburg]]''' defeated {{flagicon|SWE}} [[Ronnie Båthman]] / {{flagicon|SWE}} [[Rikard Bergh]] 6&ndash;3, 6&ndash;4
* It was Odizor's 2nd title of the year and the 8th of his career. It was van Rensburg's 2nd title of the year and the 16th of his career.

