'''Club Social y Deportivo Mixco''' is a [[Guatemala]]n [[Football (soccer)|football]] club based in [[Mixco]], [[Guatemala Department|Guatemala]].

In 2018 was founded their new stadium '''Santo Domingo de Guzmán''', until then they played at the [[Estadio Municipal de San Miguel Petapa|Estadio Julio Armando Cobar]]<ref>[http://www.lared.com.gt/detalle_noticia.php?id=25686 Mixco jugará en el estadio Julio A. Cobar] – La Red Deportiva {{es icon}}</ref> in [[San Miguel Petapa]].<ref>[http://deportivomixco.com/desplieganews.php?codigo=49 Estadio del Deportivo Mixco] – Deportivo Mixco {{es icon}}</ref>

In the Apertura 2010 they played their home games at the '''Estadio Municipal San Miguel Dueñas'''.<ref>[http://www.lared.com.gt/detalle_noticia.php?id=31461 Mixco jugará en San Miguel Dueñas] – La Red Deportiva {{es icon}}</ref>

==History==
Nicknamed ''Los Halcones'' (the Hawks), the club was founded in 1964<ref>[http://deportivomixco.com/historia.php History] – Deportivo Mixco {{es icon}}</ref> and made their debut at the [[Primera División de Ascenso|Guatemalan second level]] in the 2001/2002 season. They relegated in 2003 but got back in 2005<ref>[http://www.rsssf.com/tablesg/guat05.html Guatemala 2004/05] – RSSSF</ref> and have stayed there since.

