{{Infobox athlete | name = Harvey Dixon | image = EKB21212 debjani (29885785277).jpg | imagesize = | caption = Harvey Dixon in 2018 | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1993|11|2|df=yes}} | birth_place = [[Nice]], [[France]] | height = 1.76 m<ref>{{cite web|url=https://results.gc2018.com/en/athletics/athlete-profile-n6008692-harvey-dixon.htm?source=mobile_app|title=2018 CWG bio|accessdate=23 April 2018}}</ref> | weight = 63 kg | sport = [[Athletics (sport)|Athletics]] | event = [[1500 metres]] | club = [[Aldershot, Farnham and District Athletics Club|Aldershot, Farnham & District AC]]<ref>[http://www.thepowerof10.info/athletes/profile.aspx?athleteid=65896 Power of 10 profile]</ref> | coach = [[Geoff Wightman]] | education = [[Providence College]] | collegeteam = [[Providence Friars]] | medaltemplates = }} '''Harvey Dixon''' (born 2 November 1993) is a [[Gibraltar]]ian [[Middle-distance running|middle-distance runner]] who competes primarily in the [[1500 metres]].<ref>{{iaaf name|257425}}</ref> He represented his country at the [[2017 World Championships in Athletics|2017 World Championships]] failing to qualify for the next round despite setting a new [[List of Gibraltarian records in athletics|national record]].
In April 2018, he became the first athlete from Gibraltar to reach a final at the [[Commonwealth Games]], when he qualified for the [[Athletics at the 2018 Commonwealth Games – Men's 1500 metres|men's 1500 metres]] at the [[2018 Commonwealth Games|Gold Coast games]]. He finished in eleventh place, setting a new national record in the process.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://chronicle.gi/2018/04/gib-athlete-makes-1500m-final-as-2018-commonwealth-games-come-to-a-close/ |title=Gib athlete makes 1500m final as 2018 Commonwealth Games come to a close |work=Gibraltar Chronicle |accessdate=14 April 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://chronicle.gi/2018/04/dixon-beats-1500m-national-record-at-commonweath-games-final/ |title=Dixon beats 1500m National Record at Commonweath Games final |work=Gibraltar Chronicle |accessdate=14 April 2018}}</ref>
