{{Underlinked|date=January 2018}} {{IIHFnation |IIHFnation = United Arab Emirates |logo_image = |organization = UAE Ice Sports Federation |code = UAE |joined = May 10, 2001 |president = Ahmed Mubarak Al Mazrouei |mens_ranking = 46 |womens_ranking = |website = http://www.uaeisf.com/ }}
The '''UAE Ice Sports Federation''' (UAEISF) ({{lang-ar|اتحاد الامارات للرياضات الجليدية}}) is recognized as the official authority for all ice hockey activities within the [[United Arab Emirates]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nhl.com/ice/m_news.htm?id=615662 |title=Hockey finds an unlikely home in Arabian Gulf - NHL.com - News |website=NHL.com |date= |accessdate=2016-10-17}}</ref><ref>[http://khaleejtimes.com/sport/local/uae-ice-hockey-ass ]{{dead link|date=October 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://gulfnews.com/news/uae/general/new-ghantoot-ice-rink-in-ice-hockey-association-plans-1.417781 |title=New Ghantoot ice rink in Ice Hockey Association plans |website=GulfNews.com |date=2001-05-30 |accessdate=2016-10-17}}</ref>
The UAEISF actively encourages the UAE nationals to participate and gives them the opportunities through recruitment, training, competitive sporting programs, role models and international exposure as members of the [[United Arab Emirates men's national ice hockey team|UAE national team]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bt.com.bn/features/2012/07/07/ice-hockey-rise-middle-east |title=Ice Hockey on the rise in the Middle East &#124; The Brunei Times |website=Bt.com.bn |date=2012-07-07 |accessdate=2016-10-17 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161018211230/http://www.bt.com.bn/features/2012/07/07/ice-hockey-rise-middle-east |archivedate=2016-10-18 |df= }}</ref>
