{{Infobox cricket ground | ground_name = West Park | nickname = | country = England | image = | location = [[West Bridgford]], [[Nottinghamshire]] | establishment = 1928 <small>(first recorded match)</small> | seating_capacity = | end1 = | end2 = | year1 = 1932 & 1935 | club1 = [[Julien Cahn|Sir J Cahn's XI]] | date = 30 August | year = 2010 | source = https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/834.html Ground profile }}
'''West Park''' is a [[cricket]] ground in [[West Bridgford]], [[Nottinghamshire]]. The ground was constructed by cricket philanthropist [[Julien Cahn|Sir Julien Cahn]]. The first recorded match on the ground was in 1928, when [[Julien Cahn|Sir J Cahn's XI]] played the touring [[West Indies cricket team|West Indians]] in a non first-class match.<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/834_misc.html Other matches played on West Park]</ref> In 1932 the ground held its first [[first-class cricket|first-class]] match when Sir J Cahn's XI played the [[South American cricket team in England in 1932|touring South Americans]]. The ground held 2 further first-class matches, both of which came in 1935 when Sir J Cahn's XI played [[Leicestershire County Cricket Club|Leciestershire]] and [[Lancashire County Cricket Club|Lancashire]].<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/834_f.html First-Class matches played on West Park]</ref> Sir J Cahn's XI last played at the ground in 1941 when they took on a British Empire XI.
Still in use to this day, the ground is owned by Rushcliffe Borough Council.<ref>[http://www.rushcliffe.gov.uk/doc.asp?doc=5599 West Park - Rushcliffe.gov]</ref>
